The paper addresses the problem of large-scale image retrieval, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves the fusion of global and local cues, which is a common approach in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method also involves adaptive weighting, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
